statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.name: turnovers
statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

statistics.name: assistTurnoverRatio
statistics.description: The average number of assists a player or team records per turnover

statistics.description: The total number of rebounds (offensive and defensive).

statistics.description: The number of times when the defense obtains the possession of the ball after a missed shot by the offense.

article.headline: UC Davis 71, UC Santa Cruz 49
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. (AP) -- Freshman Mark Payne had 14 points, six steals, five rebounds, and three assists to lead UC Davis over Santa Cruz 71-49 on Sunday. David Carter added 12 points and six rebounds and Shane Hanson had 11 points and three rebounds for the Aggies (2-2). After Payne converted a steal into a score, UC Davis led 46-28 at the 16:18 mark in the second half. The Banana Slugs roared back to cut the Aggies lead 50-44 on a 3-point shot by guard Carlos Leon Jr., but Shane Hanson's three-pointer with 6:49 remaining ignited a 17-0 run that kept the Aggies ahead for good. Payne and Michael Boone had eight points apiece to guide UC Davis to a 35-26 halftime lead. Senior forward Jon Morrison led UC Santa Cruz (0-1) with 11 points.
